U.K. Chancellor of the Exchequer
 George Osborne  said his deficit-reduction plan can survive the
economic slowdown.  Speaking to reporters in  Washington  today, he said monetary
policy and the automatic stabilizers -- the lower tax burden and
higher spending on welfare that happens during periods of
weakness -- would support the economy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gonzalo Vina in London at 
